commitResults.messageBody: Remove trailing whitespace on line 8 and added newline to EOF

The applicant class is essentially the same as the previous person class.

Refactoring the Person class to the Applicant class better reflects our application's data model, and builds the foundation for adding more features, such as the Job class.

Testing for the Applicant class is also added, and the tests are still essentially the same as the Person class. To aid in the testing, the classes TypicalApplicants and ApplicantBuilder have been created, but without AddressBook dependencies. That must be added in a future commit/PR.
Refactor package name from seedu.address to seedu.linkedout

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix JSON Property Person to Applicant
commitResults.messageBody:
This change allows the read and save tests for LinkedOUT to pass.

The reason the tests were failing is because the JSON reads a person object and cannot load a person object into the applicant object. Likewise when saving to storage, the expected value is a person not an applicant. Changing the test file changes expected values to applicant.
Update JsonRootName

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Stage and Job fields to relevant classes
commitResults.messageBody:
SampleDataUtil had copies of addresses strings for job and stage fields. Same with typical applicants.

These have been updated to match the expectation for what is constituted as a job or a stage in a job interview.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change job validation regex to alphanumeric
commitResults.messageBody:
Jobs should be named without special characters, as is common in real life.

Edit validation regex for jobs to reflect this change. Refactor test utils such as typicalApplicants and JSON files, so that jobs only contain alphanumeric characters.
Added a suite of tests in order to check for invalid non-alphanumeric inputs.
Change message constraints to match the change in regex from 'anything goes' to alphanumeric only
